    <h1>Standards For Robot Framework Portability</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div style=3D"display: none;">
<br>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"StandardsForRobotFrameworkPortability-AllTestCodeShouldBeReviewed=
AndMeetTheDefinitionofDone">All Test Code Should Be Reviewed And Meet The D=
efinition of Done</h1>
<ul>
<li>Test Code should meet all the standards of product code in both style a=
nd quality.</li>
<li>"Definition of Done" in this context means that the test code is comple=
te and functioning as designed.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"StandardsForRobotFrameworkPortability-AllTestsShouldBeActivelyExe=
cutedAsPartOfRegularTestingInitiatives">All Tests Should Be Actively Execut=
ed As Part Of Regular Testing Initiatives</h1>
<ul>
<li>Any test considered for usability should be code that is regularly exec=
uted and part of the release cycle.</li>
<li>It should live as part of a Jenkins Job or other planned test cycle of =
the team.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"StandardsForRobotFrameworkPortability-CodeWrittenPrimarilyInRobot=
FrameworkShouldBeIsolated">Code Written Primarily In Robot Framework Should=
 Be Isolated</h1>
<ul>
<li>Both Tests and Resources written in Robot Framework should be able to b=
e ported to another project with minimal refactoring.</li>
<li>Introducing RF code from one project to another should not result in al=
tering either of the projects negatively.</li>
<li>The code should be completely contained in easy to move Resource/Test f=
olders.</li>
<li>If the RF library is to be shared by more than one project it is advise=
d to refactor it as a python based library and packaged as a pip installabl=
e library.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"StandardsForRobotFrameworkPortability-RobotFrameworkLibrariesWrit=
tenInPythonShouldBeIsolated">Robot Framework Libraries Written In Python Sh=
ould Be&nbsp;Isolated</h1>
<ul>
<li>Python based Robot Framework custom libraries should meet the Python st=
yle and code quality.</li>
<li>The library should follow the best practices put forth by the Robot Fra=
mework user guide.</li>
<li>If possible, the library should be packaged as a pip installable librar=
y.</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"StandardsForRobotFrameworkPortability-TestCodeShouldBeSystemAgnos=
tic">Test Code Should Be System Agnostic</h1>
<ul>
<li>Tests can be executed against an application regardless of system domai=
n</li>
<li>There might be limitations in regards to application version though (i.=
e. new functionality, different functionality, etc ...)</li>
<li>It may be necessary to implement test data portability in conjunction w=
ith tests.</li>
</ul>
